The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses revenue and welfare optimization, which are central topics in economics, suggesting cs.EC (Economics and Computation) as a possible sub-category.
